title: Yield of Dreams
text: Of the 10 banks recently surveyed by Bloomberg News, six expect the 10-year Treasury yield to finish 2020 at 1.75% or below. Societe Generale is forecasting yields will fall more than 60 bps to 1.20%, making new all-time lows. On the other side, Goldman Sachs projects yields to climb about 40 bps to 2.25%.
